SALESFORCE USEFUL CLI COMMANDS :

* [to update CLI version]
sfdx update

* [lists all top-level topics]
sfdx --help | -h

* [is sfdx cli installed or not? or check the updated version]
sfdx --version | -v

* []
sfdx alias:list

* [auth connections]
sfdx auth:list    list auth connection information
sfdx auth:logout  log out from authorized orgs

* [authorize an org using a web browser]
sfdx auth:web:login      

* [lists all the topics under force]
sfdx force --help  

* [to check all the connected orgs with this file]
sfdx force:org:list
sfdx force:org:list --all

* [login/ authorize an dev org or sandbox with the connected file(at terminal)]
sfdx force:auth:web:login --setalias <hub_org_name> --instanceurl https://login.salesforce.com
sfdx force:auth:web:login --setalias <sandbox_name> --instanceurl https://test.salesforce.com

* [to set the alias name]
sfdx force:config:set defaultusername=my-sandbox

*[to deploy or retrive the component files to/from org using metadata type... Here -m stands for metadata]
sfdx force:source:deploy -m CustomObject,ApexClass,ApexTrigger,ApexPage,CustomLabels,AuraDefinitionBundle
sfdx force:source:retrieve -m CustomObject,ApexClass,ApexTrigger,ApexPage,CustomLabels,AuraDefinitionBundle
  
